snippet.textDisplay:
Quick answer on Birds of Prey: my partner & my little brother work weekends, that simple. We're going to see it on one of their days off this week, and we're super stoked for it.


Longer answer: They're both dudes and I'm pretty sure they're somehow more excited for it than I am. So that whole "woke" argument is bullshit. DC's recent track record of just destroying their characters in movies is why we haven't one of the DC superhero movies in theaters (save for Aquaman when it went to the discount theater) in years, because they've just been so bad. The fact that we want to see Birds speaks volumes considering how little we've wanted to go near DC films in recent years (love their TV shows tho).
